On command Prompt Window:

	1. To know the git version installed:
    git --version

	2. Configuring .gitconfig file with various fields 
	a. Username : $ git config --global user.name "Your Name"
	b. Email: $ git config --global user.email "Your mail ID"
	c. Display current configuration settings on your GIT:  $ git config --list 
	(Git will output a list of all configuration settings currently set on your system.)
	
	3. To display the already set config settings on your GIT:
	a. $ git config user.name - displays user name set in .gitconfig
	b. $ git config user.email - displays user emain set in .gitconfig

	4. To go in the file path where this .gitconfile is present
	$ cd ~
	
	5. List the file content in the path:
	$ ls -la
	
	6. To open the any file to view its content
	cat .gitconfig \
	
	7. To set your default editor for Git Popups:
	$ git config --global core.editor "notepad.exe" 
	
	8. To enable colored output for Git commands globally on your system:
	$ git config --global color.ui true

	9. To list down common GIT commands for various situations
  $ git help 
